<TITLE> Mobile networks restored after 5-hour break </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Feb 26 (bdnews24.com)Mobile networks restored after 5-hour break. The operators were earlier restricting calls from the capital to other parts of the country and to BDR's headquarters in Dhaka, from midday Thursday, said officials. Grameenphone said mobile services were shut off nationwide, except for some areas of the capital, according to a government directive. A Warid official told bdnews24.com that instructions had also come from the home ministry to shutdown all network communication with BDR's headquarters in the capital. Banglalink and Citycell officals said they were also limiting their networks to Dhaka. bdn
